  "workflow_metadata": {
    "title": "SeedVR2 NVFP4 High-Performance Workflow (RTX 50 Series)",
    "description": "Optimized for RTX 5070 Ti / 5080 / 5090 with NVFP4 acceleration. This workflow demonstrates:\n\n• NVFP4 model for 2-2.5x speedup over FP8\n• Flash Attention 3 for optimal Blackwell performance\n• Batch size of 20 frames (3-4x larger than FP16)\n• ~6GB VRAM usage (60-70% reduction vs FP16)\n• LAB color correction for best quality\n\nPerformance Expectations (RTX 5070 Ti):\n- Processing Speed: 2-2.5x faster than FP8\n- VRAM Usage: 5-6GB (vs 16GB FP16)\n- Batch Size: 15-20 frames (vs 5 FP16)\n- Quality: 98-99% of FP16 output\n\nRequirements:\n- RTX 50 series GPU (5070/5070 Ti/5080/5090)\n- Optional: TensorRT-LLM for native NVFP4 kernels\n  pip install tensorrt-llm>=0.14.0\n\nConfiguration Notes:\n- Attention mode set to flash_attn_3 for Blackwell\n- Batch size set to 20 for optimal temporal consistency\n- Color correction set to 'lab' for best quality\n- VAE offload to CPU reduces VRAM overhead",
    "author": "SeedVR2 Team",
    "version": "2.5.24",
    "tags": ["nvfp4", "blackwell", "rtx-50", "high-performance", "video-upscaling"]
  }
